    :content
    "# Environment extension

Pkg: `com.blockether/vis-common-environment`. Src: `extensions/common/vis-common-environment/`. Canonical: inlined under `[environment :docs \"README.md\"]` in `META-INF/vis-extension/vis.edn`. LLM reads via `(meta/extension-readme 'environment)`.

Owns the `<environment>` block in the system prompt. Replaces the old hard-coded six-line block in `com.blockether.vis.internal.prompt/environment-block`. Adds three things the old block lacked:

1. **Git repo awareness** via JGit — root, branch (or detached HEAD sha), dirty-status counts, submodule presence, linked-worktree detection.
2. **Language stats** — bounded scan of working tree counting files+bytes per language, sorted by total bytes, with primary-language pick.
3. **Monorepo detection** — counts of per-ecosystem manifests (`deps.edn`, `package.json`, `Cargo.toml`, `pyproject.toml`, `go.mod`, ...) below repo root + shape label (`polylith`, `workspace`, `submodules`).

Both prompt block and sandbox surface read one cached snapshot keyed by canonical `cwd`.

## Prompt block

Dense, conditional. No git repo / empty scan / single-package -> corresponding lines drop:

```
<environment>
  cwd: /Users/me/projects/foo (= git root)
  user: me (home: /Users/me)
  platform: Mac OS X 14.5 (aarch64) | shell: /bin/zsh | locale: en-US
  jvm: OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM 21.0.4
  git.root: /Users/me/projects/foo
  git.branch: main
  git.status: dirty (3 modified, 2 untracked)
  git: submodules: false | worktree: false
  languages: clojure 78% (1234 files), markdown 12% (89 files), edn 6% (45 files), shell 4% (12 files)
  primary-language: clojure
  monorepo: polylith — clojure: 8
</environment>
```

## Sandbox surface

`environment/` alias.

### Snapshot

`(environment/snapshot)` -> full structured map:

```clojure
{:host      {:cwd :user :home :os-name :os-version :os-arch
             :shell :jvm :locale}
 :git       {:root :git-dir :branch :detached? :detached-sha
             :submodules? :worktree?
             :clean? :modified :untracked :added :changed
             :missing :removed :conflicting}      ;; or nil
 :languages {:total-files :total-bytes :truncated? :elapsed-ms
             :primary :languages [...]}           ;; or nil
 :monorepo  {:shape :totals :files :truncated?}}  ;; :shape nil for single-package
```

Cached per canonical `cwd`. Recomputed automatically when cwd changes.

### Submap accessors

```clojure
(environment/git)        ;; :git submap or nil
(environment/languages)  ;; :languages submap
(environment/monorepo)   ;; :monorepo submap
```

Conveniences over `(get (environment/snapshot) :…)`.

### Refresh

`(environment/refresh!)` drops cache, recomputes. Use after long task that changed working tree (new files, branch checkout, etc.).

### Render

`(environment/render)` -> the same `<environment>` block as a string. Useful for debugging / surfacing the block on demand in `:code`.

## Boundaries + guarantees

- **No exception leaks.** Each section (host/git/languages/monorepo) independently guarded. One failure -> `nil` for that section, no poisoning.
- **Bounded scans.** Language scan: 1s wall-time deadline + 10000 max files. Monorepo scan: 800ms deadline. JGit `git status`: side thread, 2s timeout — huge dirty trees drop dirty-status fields rather than blocking system-prompt build.
- **Cache locality.** Snapshot cached at ext scope, keyed by canonical `cwd`. Multiple conversations in same process share one cache entry per dir.

## Use when

- Need to know which repo / branch -> `(environment/git)` (one read; no shell-out).
- Decide which language conventions apply before write/edit -> `(:primary (environment/languages))` (no `ls -R`).
- Suspect monorepo, want shape -> `(:shape (environment/monorepo))` (no manual tree walk).

## Don't use when

- Real-time diff inspection. JGit is not exposed as a tool here; editing ext exposes filesystem reads and a full git client surface lives outside this ext's scope.
- Cross-repository / workspace-of-workspaces analysis. Reports the repo containing JVM cwd and nothing else.

## Implementation notes

- **JGit version** pinned to same coordinate `vis-common-editing`'s `.gitignore` parser uses -> one resolved version on classpath.
- **Reflection-clean.** All JGit + NIO call sites typed; ext contributes 0 new GraalVM warnings to verify baseline.
- **No SCI-side I/O concentration.** `:ext/prompt` fragment reads same cache as sandbox accessors -> exactly one tree walk per `(refresh!)` boundary."

